PEOPLE of the United States ex rel. Tauba ALTMAN, Alien, Relator-Appellee, v. Robert E. TOD, Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of New York, Respondent-Appellant. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 21, 1924.) No. 237. William Hayward, U. S. Atty., of New York City (James C. Thomas, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Chas. J. Katzensteih, of New York City, for appellee.

Be-fore ROGERS, MANTON, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PÍ1R CURIAM.

Order is modified, and the case remanded to the District Court, with directions to proceed in accordance with the opinion of this court in United States ex rel. Engel v. Tod, 294 Fed. 820.
